{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b5cd084-b92f-4426-b5fe-523a7afc9d40","content":"Here's the recommended setup for MSTest with parallel-by-default execution and sequential database tests:\n\n### 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` meta-package pulls in the SDK, runner, and assertions — no need to list them separately.\n\n### 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>\n      <Scope>ClassLevel</Scope>\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\n- **Workers=0** → uses the number of logical processors.\n- **Scope=ClassLevel** → test classes run in parallel; tests *within* a class run sequentially (safest default).\n\nYou can also set this via assembly attribute instead of `.runsettings`:\n\n```csharp\n// In a file like AssemblyInfo.cs or Usings.cs\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n### 3. Make database tests sequential\n\nMark your DB test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Should_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Should_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n`[DoNotParallelize]` ensures that class runs alone — no other test classes execute concurrently with it.\n\n### Key points\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` or `.runsettings` |\n| Sequential DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n| Scope choice | `ClassLevel` is safest; `MethodLevel` is faster but requires fully independent tests |\n\nRun with: `dotnet test` (picks up `.runsettings` automatically if in the project root), or explicitly: `dotnet test --settings .runsettings`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8a5154e1-e01c-4b2c-b2b3-a7953b74a43e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty. The user is asking for general guidance on setting up an MSTest project. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.","outputTokens":688,"requestId":"1BCB:C0207:23989E9:276038D:6A03DA94"},"id":"5d82519b-14e1-48a6-a623-9cdb47809d7a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:57:53.718Z","parentId":"63a83990-d80f-4a47-b360-176678402546"}
